subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Vertical process of gonopod apically small, nearly membraneous, only with 1 projection per side (
Fig. 33D
); 2 pairs of basal bridges of aedeagal median rod fused to each other (
Fig. 33D
).

Description.
Frons dark brown above, brownish below. Face brownish. Mesoscutum, pleura, and scutellum brownish yellow, with brown to dark brown patches and pollinose pattern. Male terminalia (
Fig. 33
): Epandrium pubescent anteroventrally, with ca. 10 setae on dorsal to posterolateral portion per side (
Fig. 33B
). Surstylus lacking pubescence on outer surface, with several wedge-like prensisetae on apical margin and inner surface (
Fig. 33C
). Paramere expanded distally; apical process with 2 sensilla and 1 tooth; medial process with 2 sensilla, lacking pubescence or tooth; basal process acute apically (
Fig. 33E
). Aedeagal median rod with 2 slightly asymmetrical processes submedially (
Fig. 33D
).
